This article is a Presidential Proclamation by Barack Obama declaring March 31st as Cesar Chavez Day in honor of the civil rights activist. It highlights Chavez's work as a champion for social justice and his fight for the rights of migrant farm workers. The proclamation also mentions his role in founding the United Farm Workers and leading a successful grape boycott. Obama emphasizes the importance of Chavez's values and encourages Americans to participate in service projects and education programs to honor his legacy. The proclamation concludes with the official declaration of Cesar Chavez Day.